). Endemic to southern Africa but has been introduced to Australia and was introduced as a garden plant to North America in the early 20th century and now globally available through commercial seeds from online sources under the name "Garden Huckleberry".

Berries used raw and for jam (
Viljoen 2011
); leaves eaten as a pot-herb vegetable.

